pan class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 191<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 7:32:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 49 Equipment check(please)</span><hr size=1> Well lets see...<br>
<br>
Face: Trash. Sell it to a WIS caster, and buy at least Fine Plate 7 AC for about 70pp (or go to Runnyeye and get a Grotesque Alloy mask for free. Has 6 AC 7 DEX 5 SvMagic and -15 CHA, I wear it over Fine Plate because I don't seem to lose any AC).<br>
<br>
Neck: Get Ry'Gorr (this will also boost your STA to 100, so you will stop getting bad effects when your yellow bar drops to yellow), should run around 250pp.<br>
<br>
Rings: Get 6ac 65 hp rings. Should run up to 1k for 2.<br>
<br>
Hands: Gaunts of Black &gt; DW gaunts. Sell DW gaunts to buy them and you will still have money to spare.<br>
<br>
Legs: Get crusty, you'll love the HP you gain from the 16 STA, and the STR on it is good too. 16 STA/6  STR &gt; 1 ac. Keep Ro around for save gear though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Belt/neck/back: Get spider fur for all these slots. 10 AC each with stats, including 40 HP belt. Also will get your dex up a bit, which is  good for the proc spells that I hope you are using <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  BTW your cloak &gt; my cloak hehe<br>
<br>
Bracer 1: your STR is good enough; I would replace this with Bracer of Scavenging (same AC, 5 DEX 5 of that all-important STA)<br>
Bracer 2/helm/boots: Keep.<br>
<br>
Ears: Ah, the ear question. Here it's a matter of preference. Orc fangs are good, considering the HP and other stats you are losing by making your visible pieces Deepwater. Alternative would be Wolf Fang Earrings,  4 AC 3 STR 2 STA.<br>
<br>
Shoulder: option 1: tattered mantle (not the newbie gear one) option 2: crested spaulders<br>
<br>
Range: Goranga Idol. Anything with AC really.<br>
<br>
BP: Enameled Black Chestplate or Treeweave. Same AC, treeweave weighs less and has 10 STR but looks, well... and EBCP looks good.<br>
<br>
Weapon: Yeah, ACG is a good choice. Alternatively, get a STR of Grodan from Maiden's Eye (people say 50+ zone, but if you form your own groups you should be able to kick some butt, I know I am able to at level 4<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Lastly...<br>
<br>
YOU NEED HASTE! (I don't have haste, and I've paid the price many times over)<br>
However, do NOT buy a Flowing Red Silk Sash (6% haste) or a lesser guard of haste (6% haste). Those are pretty much trash. Get an FBSS, or preferably, SChandwraps (FBSS = 21% haste with no stats, SCWraps =22% haste, 5 AC, 3 svall.) However, the wraps are likely to cost you about twice as much as an FBSS. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 9:02:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 49 Equipment check(please)</span><hr size=1> Greetings!<br>
<br>
Balidin pretty-much hit on everything I might recomend, however...<br>
<br>
It appears that the SoG drop rate has been nerfed through the floor.  However, go to ME anyway and try getting:<br>
Slighted Pauldrons<br>
Axgoroth's Belt of Defence<br>
Goranga Idol<br>
Centi Warspear<br>
<br>
If you can get on a Plane of Sky raid at all, do so!  The Symbol of Marr is (apparently) a pretty common drop. (AC 15, +5 Str, +5 Wis, Neck slot)<br>
<br>
As for which Velious faction to go for... that's normally a Guild-level question, not a personal question.  If your Guild is going Giant faction... I would try and persuade them against it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Skyshrine Armour (Dragon Faction) is a bit easier to get and over-all better for most every class (except <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> maybe</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pure Warriors &amp; Monks).  Getting Thurgadin Quest Armour is even easier, and raids on Kael are fairly commonplace. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 4:23:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 49 Equipment check(please)</span><hr size=1> PS. I did not kick butt in ME with my group at level 4<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  That was supposed to be level 48. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I hate EZcodes sometimes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udebbin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Debbin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 4:53:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://128.211.226.38/pics/deb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 49 Equipment check(please)</span><hr size=1> heh, yeah.  Thanks for the tips and info, most definately useful.  What is the lowest I should let my str fall?  I really notice very little difference from when my str was about 130 to now that its at 154. <p>Debbin Lifeblade, Paladin of 49 seasons</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzosa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zosa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/02 1:00:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 49 Equipment check(please)</span><hr size=1> One thing other guys did not mention, secure yourself a haste item above all else. Sacrifice AC, stats, get a haste item. Junk the stats items and go for AC gear.<br>
 <p>Varutia Silvonesit<BR>
Level 55 Knight<BR>
Terris Thule<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utramausvoronadil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tramaus Voronadil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/02 1:24:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 49 Equipment check(please)</span><hr size=1> Quick question about the neck slot then. Which would be better for a Paladin?<br>
<br>
Chipped Velium Amulet<br>
AC4 +4 STR +30 HP<br>
<br>
Orc Fang Necklace<br>
AC5 +3 STR/STA/AGI<br>
<br>
Rygorr Chain Collar<br>
AC9 +4 STA + 4 sv. Magic + 10 Mana<br>
<br>
On raw AC obviously the collar wins but the Fang Necklace has a nice combination of stats. I'm just wondering which one would be better. I have the Chipped Velium Amulet right now (+30 HP is nice) and I'm wondering if upgrading to either the Necklace or the Collar would be a good idea?<br>
<br>
Tramaus Voronadil<br>
45th Paladin of Truth - Order of Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udpawson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dpawson</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/02 1:31:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.pattyanddave.com/dave/lr/pics/ZsaFace.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 49 Equipment check(please)</span><hr size=1> Others are free to disagree, but I'd say the difference between the Ry'gorr Collar and the Orc Fang Necklace isn't even close.<br>
<br>
AC: Ry'gorr blows the doors off the Orc Fang.<br>
STR: Orc Fang wins, it doesn't matter at all unless you're lugging yourself around encumbered. Those 3 strength will do you almost no good.<br>
STA: Ry'gorr has more, that means more hp.<br>
AGI: Orc Fang wins, but all this will do is get you slightly better AC, nowhere near enough to make up for the AC difference.<br>
SVM: Ry'gorr gives you this. More and more important as you level.<br>
MANA: Why not? Ry'gorr throws this in as an added bonus.<br>
<br>
Look at it like this: the 3 AGI on the Orc Fang might possibly make up for 1 of the AC on the Ry'gorr. So you end up trading 3 STR against AC3, STA1, SVM4, MANA10. That's not close.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps!<br>
